# Custom Hooks Standards

## Three Hook Types, Three Responsibilities

| Hook | File | Tech | Purpose |
|------|------|------|---------|
| Data | `useFeatureData.ts` | React Query `useQuery` | Fetch and cache |
| Mutations | `useFeatureMutations.ts` | React Query `useMutation` | Create, update, delete |
| Form | `useFeatureForm.ts` | plain `useState` | Form state and validation |

See `react-query.mdc` for full `useFeatureData` and `useFeatureMutations` patterns.

## Form Hook Pattern

```typescript
const INITIAL: FeatureFormData = { title: '', description: '' };

export const useFeatureForm = () => {
  const [form, setForm] = useState<FeatureFormData>(INITIAL);

  const updateField = <K extends keyof FeatureFormData>(
    field: K,
    value: FeatureFormData[K]
  ) => setForm(prev => ({ ...prev, [field]: value }));

  const resetForm = () => setForm(INITIAL);

  const loadForEdit = (item: Feature) =>
    setForm({ title: item.title, description: item.description });

  const isValid = form.title.trim().length > 0;

  return { form, updateField, resetForm, loadForEdit, isValid };
};
```

`loadForEdit` pre-fills the form when editing an existing item. `resetForm` returns to `INITIAL` state on cancel/submit.

## Common Reusable Hooks

Check `hooks/` before creating a new hook:

- `useForm` — generic form state management
- `useAuthGuard` — redirect unauthenticated users (web)
- `useModal` — modal open/close with optional typed payload
- `useDebounce` — debounced value
- `usePagination` — pagination state

### useModal Destructuring

Always destructure `useModal` — never access via dot notation:

✅ **GOOD:**

```typescript
const {
  isOpen: isDeleteOpen,
  open: openDelete,
  close: closeDelete,
  payload: deleteId,
} = useModal<string>();

openDelete(item.id);
```

❌ **BAD:**

```typescript
const deleteModal = useModal<string>();
deleteModal.open(item.id); // never dot-access
```

## Manual useState vs React Query vs Zustand

- Data fetching and mutations → always React Query
- Form field state → always plain `useState`
- UI toggle state (modal open, filter selection) → plain `useState` or `useModal`
- State shared across many unrelated components with complex logic → Zustand store in `stores/`

Zustand stores live in `stores/`, not `hooks/`. Do not create a custom hook with Context lifting when Zustand is the right tool.

❌ Never use `useState` + `useEffect` for data fetching:

```typescript
// BAD
const [data, setData] = useState([]);
useEffect(() => { fetchData().then(setData); }, [user]);
```
